A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Natural Gas Generating Facilities – Authorization
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing the construction, permitting, and operation of natural gas
4 generating facilities in the State until the State meets a certain percentage of its
5 energy needs from renewable energy resources; requiring the Maryland Energy
6 Administration to work with the owners and operators of natural gas generating
7 facilities in the State to decrease the production of energy from natural gas after the
8 State meets a certain percentage of its energy needs from renewable energy
9 resources; and generally relating to natural gas generating facilities.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Public Utilities
12 Section 7–218
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – Public Utilities
18 7–218.
19 (A) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, AND SUBJECT TO
20 SUBSECTIONS (B) AND (C) OF THIS SECTION, NATURAL GAS GENERATING FACILITIES
21 MAY BE CONSTRUCTED, PERMITTED, AND OPERATED IN THE STATE UNTIL THE
22 STATE MEETS 50% OF ITS ENERGY NEEDS FROM RENEWABLE ENERGY RESOURCES,
23 INCLUDING NUCLEAR ENERGY.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1217*

2 HOUSE BILL 1217
1 (B) A PERSON CONSTRUCTING A NATURAL GAS GENERATING FACILITY
2 UNDER THIS SECTION MUST OBTAIN:
3 (1) A CERTIFICATE OF PUBLIC CONVENIENCE AND NECESSITY UNDER
4 § 7–207 OF THIS SUBTITLE; OR
5 (2) COMMISSION APPROVAL UNDER § 7–207.1 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
6 (C) ONCE THE STATE MEETS 50% OF ITS ENERGY NEEDS FROM RENEWABLE
7 ENERGY RESOURCES, INCLUDING NUCLEAR ENERGY, THE MARYLAND ENERGY
8 ADMINISTRATION SHALL WORK WITH THE OWNERS AND OPERATORS OF NATURAL
9 GAS GENERATING FACILITIES IN THE STATE TO DECREASE THE PRODUCTION OF
10 ENERGY FROM NATURAL GAS GENERATING FACILITIES AT THE SAME RATE AS
11 ENERGY PRODUCED FROM RENEWABLE ENERGY RESOURCES, INCLUDING NUCLEAR
12 ENERGY, IS INCREASED.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
14 October 1, 2025.

